Package: tableHTML
Type: Package
Title: A Tool to Create HTML Tables
Version: 1.0.1
Authors@R: person("Theo", 
                  "Boutaris", 
                  email = "teoboot2007@hotmail.com", 
                  role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
URL: https://lyzander.github.io/tableHTML                  
BugReports: https://github.com/LyzandeR/tableHTML/issues
Depends: R (>= 3.2.0)
Imports: htmltools,
         magrittr,
         shiny
Description: tableHTML can be used to create and style HTML tables with CSS. HTML tables can be exported and used in any application that accepts HTML.
             It is compatible with shiny and rmarkdown. It also provides functions to create CSS files and add those to shiny. 
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: TRUE
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
Suggests: testthat,
          knitr,
          rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
